<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="125" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,686,1110]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,563,830,857]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Diagnosis (
<figureCitation box="[329,416,830,857]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–27" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[326,1290,214,1760]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[195,1392,181,1910]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 22–27. Head, group dispar: 22. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 23. A. dispar, 24. A. insuturatus, 25. A. schwarzi, 26. A. taeniopygus, 27. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557881/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 26</figureCitation>
, 69, 95, 101)
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="1999" box="[577,851,831,857]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taeniopygus">
<emphasis box="[577,851,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Amblycerus taeniopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the internal sac of male genitalia without sclerites in the apical region (
<figureCitation box="[585,674,866,893]" captionStart="FIGURES 91–96" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[166,1404,385,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1435,373,1900]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 91–96. Male genitalia, median lobe, group dispar: 91. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 92. A. dispar, 93. A. insuturatus, 94. A. schwarzi, 95. A. taeniopygus and 96. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm and 500 ʯm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557907/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 95</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[688,733,867,893]" captionStart="FIGURES 97–102" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,193,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1435,174,1872]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 97–102. Male genitalia, tegmen, group dispar: 97. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 98. A. dispar, 99. A. insuturatus, 100. A. schwarzi, 101. A. taeniopygus and 102. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557909/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">101</figureCitation>
), median region with a pair of blades with denticulate, round structure and without unpaired sclerite. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="1999" box="[597,872,903,929]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taeniopygus">
<emphasis box="[597,872,903,929]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Amblycerus taeniopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[1133,1291,904,930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[1133,1291,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityName="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goianiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1346,1363,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">goianiensis</emphasis>
Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[515,578,939,965]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,578,939,965]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the internal sac of male genitalia at apical region without a pair of sclerite (present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[277,434,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insuturatus">
<emphasis box="[277,434,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A. insuturatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityName="Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2019" box="[489,925,975,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goianiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[489,506,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[520,648,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">goianiensis</emphasis>
Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[936,999,975,1001]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[936,999,975,1001]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
